FG-131 — Pre-Filing QC Gate (5 Checks, 10 Minutes)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: A fast QC gate prevents 80% of returns and confusion.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Five checks: (1) Caption consistent, (2) Pins per paragraph, (3) Relief two lines pasted, (4) Attachments PDF/A + bookmarks + Title, (5) Signature/Service complete.
	•	📝 Assignment: Print a 5-item QC card and tape it above your export button.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Caption ✓ Pins ✓ Relief ✓ PDF/A+bookmarks ✓ Signature+Service ✓.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Ten minutes here saves days later.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A five-checkbox strip with all green.

⸻

FG-132 — Service Address Book (Parties • Counsel • Channels)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Service fights vanish when addresses and channels are built once.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Grid: Name • Role • Email • ECF ID • Mailing • Notes. Keep a courtesy-copy column for non-parties (vendors/agencies).
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a 12-row service book for your case; add it to your kit.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Opposing—Atty J (ECF; j@firm.com); Vendor X (courtesy: ops@vendor.com).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Ready addresses beat lost days.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A contact sheet with envelope/cloud icons.

⸻

FG-133 — Same-Day Hash & Index (Make It Verifiable)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Post hashes and indexes the same day you file.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: For each packet: CHECKSUMS.txt, capture date, mirror link, and a one-line legend (“PDF pages”). Add row to your public index.
	•	📝 Assignment: Generate a CHECKSUMS.txt for your last filing; post it with date.
	•	✅ Model Response: “SHA-256 41be22…; captured 08/19; mirror M-1 same hash; cites to PDF pages.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Verifiability builds trust before argument.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A fingerprint tag next to a tiny index row.

⸻

FG-134 — Bookmarks Mirror Tabs (No Easter Eggs)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Bookmarks must mirror tab names exactly.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Front page: contents + hashes; every tab gets a plain-English bookmark; remove dupes; add Back-to-Brief anchors if allowed.
	•	📝 Assignment: Audit one appendix volume; fix 5 bookmark/tab mismatches.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Tab 3 ‘Timeline’ → bookmark ‘Tab 3 — Timeline (p.2).’”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: One map, two places.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Sidebar bookmarks aligned with labeled tabs.

⸻

FG-135 — Forum-Ready Relief Bank (State • Federal • Agency)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Keep forum-specific relief text you can paste without edits.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Buckets: State (stay/supersedeas), Federal (FRAP 8/39/40), Agency (§705/Nken); each with primary + limited-remand variants; version/date.
	•	📝 Assignment: Write 5 relief snippets (decide/clarify/remand/stay/costs).
	•	✅ Model Response: “Vacate & remand for findings (a–d) within 21 days; status ≤3 pp; harm-only hearing 20 min.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Prepared text = faster signatures.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A clipboard with three forum labels and short slips.

⸻

FG-136 — Table Hygiene (Readable in 8 Seconds)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Your tables should read at a glance.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Four columns max; short headers; no wrap if possible; right-align dates; put pin in its own column; add a bottom capture/hash line for data tables.
	•	📝 Assignment: Rebuild one timeline/clock table using 4 columns and a hash footer.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Date | Event | Pin | Effect — SHA-256 41be22… (captured 08/19).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: A clean table outpersuades a page of prose.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A tidy four-column table with a fingerprint footer.

⸻

FG-137 — Source Notes & Capture Lines (Stop Link Fights)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Every quoted rule or data block needs source + captured.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Add footers to rules/statutes/guidance: official source, captured date, SHA-256 if PDF; move non-official to RJN.
	•	📝 Assignment: Add capture lines to two rule pages in your addendum.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Official source; captured 08/19; SHA-256 9f2a….”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Source notes preempt authenticity disputes.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A small “source” ribbon at the bottom of a text page.

⸻

FG-138 — Scheduling Proposals Judges Can Sign
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Propose clean dates and short windows; do the math.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Offer two schedules (10/10/7 or 7/7/3); show weekend roll-forwards; attach a tick-box order; state opponent’s position.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 2-option schedule with pin to the trigger date.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Rule 58 08/15 → reply 09/15; order attached (check one).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Good schedules get picked up verbatim.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two date strips with little checkboxes.

⸻

FG-139 — Cross-Appeal Coordination (One Voice, Two Lanes)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Make cross-appeals complementary, not duplicative.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One memo: owner per issue, mirrored headings, shared pin atlas, joint relief menu; file a short coordination note with schedule/caps.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 1-page coordination memo (owners/caps/relief).
	•	✅ Model Response: “Issue 1—Appellant; Issue 2—Cross-Appellant; caps 4k/3k/2k; joint relief menu appended.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: One map, two briefs.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two arrows labeled A/X merging into one order card.

⸻

FG-140 — Close With the Order (Top & Bottom)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Put the order text at the top of your notes and the bottom of your filing.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Draft the relief first; make the brief prove those two lines; repeat the ask in the last sentence; paste in OA card.
	•	📝 Assignment: Paste your two-line order on page 1 of your draft and at the end of the conclusion.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Vacate & remand 21 days for findings (a–d); 20-min harm hearing; status ≤3 pp.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: If it isn’t in the order, it isn’t in the brief.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A small order strip stapled to both the first and last page.